# Statistical rigor

- Run ≥3–5 seeds per arm; report mean ± 95% CI (bootstrap).
- Compare arms with paired bootstrap / permutation tests
  (`psalm.analysis.comparison_tests`), not eyeballed point estimates.
- Correct families of arm comparisons with Holm–Bonferroni at α = 0.05.
- Pre-register thresholds before seeing results; changing one requires an ADR.
- Report calibration (ECE) for Nirṇaya / confidence claims.
- Report world-knowledge benchmarks (MMLU/ARC/HellaSwag) only as honest reference
  points, framed as expected limitations — never as headline capability claims.
- An effect without uncertainty quantification is not a result.
